<TEXT>
elvis presleys involvement in the plot of jim 
jarmuschs new movie mystery train was a mystery to the 
filmmaker 
the writerdirector of stranger than paradise and down by 
law says he started with a few characters like he always does 
and came up with the idea for shooting the movie in memphis tenn 
home of presleys graceland mansion and sun studios where the 
king first recorded 
he snuck in there you got to watch out for him said the 
director at a recent press conference after the films preview at 
the new york film festival 
when i first came to memphis i went to graceland immediately 
by the time i left memphis i was so sick of elvis i never wanted 
to hear about him again 
but for now questions about jarmusch and presley are 
unavoidable 
elvis is everywhere in mystery train named after an old 
blues song that presley recorded at sun his music is on the 
soundtrack his pictures hang in hotel rooms characters see his 
ghost and johnny a workingclass englishman played by rock n 
roller joe strummer is even nicknamed elvis 
mystery train is broken into three segments which take 
place in the same time frame a young japanese couple visit memphis 
to see graceland and sun a young italian woman recently widowed 
and a talkative stranger share a hotel room for one night and 
three buddies are forced to leave town when johnny kills a liquor 
store clerk 
the japanese couple are fans theyre kind of an audience 
jarmusch says as the story progesses the way elvis is treated 
changes somwewhat by the third story johnnys saying that guy 
is everywhere 
fans of jarmuschs earlier films will quickly recognize the 
directors dark humor and fondness for characters usually found 
only in barrooms and poolhalls mystery train is however 
jarmuschs first movie shot in color 
i have to write very visually he said when i start to 
visualize the film i make an intuitive decision and i stick to 
that i cant say why if you ask someone whether they dream in 
black and white or color they cant say why i have future 
projects and i already know that some are color and some are black 
and white 
jarmusch did say he will continue to make lowbudget films 
outside the hollywood studio system he recalled a conversation 
with producer dino delaurentiis 
he asked me why do you make amateur films instead of 
professional ones i asked what made a film amateur or 
professional he said any film that costs more than 5 million is 
professional 
i guess im still making amateur films 
the cast includes elizabeth bracco rick aviles nicolette 
braschi and rhythm n blues stars screamin jay hawkins and rufus 
thomas 
mystery train is scheduled for a midnovember release by 
orion classics 
