the supreme court today rejected an appeal by 
an antipornography activist who says sexually explicit photographs 
and caricatures in hustler magazine libeled her and invaded her 
privacy 
the court without comment refused to revive a 150 million 
lawsuit by feminist author andrea dworkin 
a federal judge threw out the suit and the 9th us circuit 
court of appeals upheld the dimissal last january 
the hustler references to dworkin were opinion not statements 
of fact and therefore are protected by the freespeech guarantees 
in the constitutions first amendment the appeals court said 
dworkin errs by limiting opinion to highminded discourse 
the appeals court said 
shielding all opinion from lawsuits means that outrageous and 
outlandish statements are sometimes protected the appeals court 
said but it added ludicrous statements are much less insidious 
and debilitating than falsities that bear the ring of truth we 
have little doubt that the outrageous and outlandish will be 
recognized for what they are 
the appeals court also noted that the supreme court in 1988 
threw out a 200000 award against hustler won by television 
evangelist jerry falwell who accused the magazine of causing him 
emotional distress by publishing a pornographic parody 
in that decision the justices gave broad freespeech protection 
to parodies and satire 
dworkin said she was viciously lampooned by hustler and its 
publisher larry flynt because of her opposition to pornography 
she is the author of an indianapolis ordinance since declared 
unconstitutional that defined pornography as a violation of 
womens civil rights and permitted lawsuits against pornographers 
dworkin sued over features published in three 1984 issues of 
hustler one was a cartoon of two women engaged in lesbian sex in 
which one woman says to the other you remind me so much of 
andrea dworkin 
a second feature included a series of photographs that referred 
to the andrea dworkin fan club a photograph in a third issue 
identified a woman engaged in sex as dworkins mother 
dworkin sued in wyoming but the case was transferred to a 
federal court in los angeles at the request of hustler 
the case is dworkin vs hustler 881900 
