the law which took effect sunday gives homosexual couples 
nearly equal rights as heterosexual couples but bars them from 
adopting children they have the same inheritance rights tax 
advantages and the right to share a last name 
under the new law at least one partner must have danish 
citizenship and live in denmark 
like the other 10 couples axel and eigil solemnly answered 
yes to deputy mayor tom ahlberg when he asked if they consented 
to tie each other in a registered partnership they combined 
their first names to form a common last name 
we decided to get officially married because we have the 
same feelings for each other as heterosexual couples said axel 
speaking on danish television he and eigil later left town for 
several days friends said apparently on a honeymoon 
no lesbian couples have been registered we dont like to be 
in the front line one woman said after sundays ceremony 
the next step will be the acquisition of the right to adopt 
stepchildren from one of the partners from an earlier heterosexual 
marriage and the right to be blessed in a church said ivan 
larsen who was among the couples and is a pastor of the danish 
evangelist lutheran church 
if i had the right to marry a homosexual couple in my church 
i would certainly like to do so but for the time being well have 
to wait larsen said 
when it the partnership becomes official it lasts longer 
said larsens partner school psychologist ove carlsen who moved 
into the church parsonage two years ago 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

