<TEXT>
scores of small earthquakes shook mount 
etna on monday threatening to open a new fissure on europes most 
active volcano scientists said 
the volcano has been erupting since sept 11 coughing plumes of 
ash and lighting the night sky with spectacular fountains of lava 
down its southeastern flank officials say it poses no threat to 
nearby villages 
since sunday night there have been 30 to 35 temblors an hour on 
the volcano scientists said the quakes cracked pavement and 
forced the closure of a road used to reach sites on the 
southeastern side of the mountain 
some of the quakes had a magnitude of more than 2 on the richter 
scale of ground motion said giovanni fazzetta one of the 
scientists monitoring the eruption 
a quake of magnitude 2 on the scale which gauges the energy 
released by an earthquake as measured by a seismograph is the 
smallest normally felt by humans 
the increase in quakes could open a new lavaspilling fissure on 
the southern flank of mount etna fazzetta said 
