have never lived much less fought in a snowbound environment 
this is the hardest place on earth said modhival iqbal a 
weary 23yearold soldier who just completed four months of duty at 
a 19000foot outpost 
from the base camp soldiers armed with ice picks skis 
shovels ropes and 65pound backpacks trudge across the black 
