well as a portrait of jesus christ 
everybody who goes to the glacier comes here first and says 
his prayers it doesnt matter if hes hindu or moslem or 
christian raghavan said 
the trek takes six to eight days with brief rest stops at posts 
along the way before reaching the small outposts where the 
soldiers live for months in bunkers dug deep in the snow 
every day up there is important because every day you survive 
means youre one day closer to leaving iqbal said its not 
just the pakistanis its the blizzards the howling winds the 
blinding glare of the sun off the snow its the avalanches and the 
isolation 
we have plenty of food and supplies but not much else maybe 
