into an undemarcated area 
both pakistani and indian officials say the rapport between 
gandhi and ms bhutto is helping but it still may be difficult for 
either to yield gandhi is only months away from facing a national 
election ms bhutto is in an even stickier situation facing 
criticism at home from opposition leaders who accuse her of 
submission to india 
while their leaders struggle to find a political solution both 
sides contend they can hold out indefinitely 
whether there is a settlement is a matter between state and 
state raghavan said until then we have a job to do that 
doesnt mean we want to stay here forever who would but we can 
stay here as long as we have to 
