<TEXT>
maggie wiel is 80 nearly blind and 
cant live on her own yet she bristles at talk of a nursing home 
but wiel lives at tam house a communal home on a treelined 
street in the shadow of mount tamalpais with seven other women and 
two men its directors call tam house an idea whose time has come 
residents are simply thankful it exists 
its perfect for someone like me i needed to be around people 
but i needed to be independent and on my own said dorothy 
wright 70 who moved in 18 months ago after separating from her 
husband of 46 years 
now wright spends her time gardening playing bingo visiting 
nearby senior centers and hiking six miles a day its great to 
be able to walk to a good trout fishing lake from your home she 
said 
charlotte mulford 79 came to tam house after staying with a 
cousin on his houseboat in sausalito now she wouldnt feel 
comfortable going back if i didnt live here i couldnt afford 
to live anywhere else she said 
the 7yearold private nonprofit home owned and operated by 
the ross valley ecumenical housing association offers more 
independence than a boardandcare home while fostering 
companionship and support although there is a waiting list there 
hasnt always been communal living isnt for everyone 
it took more than a year to fill the sixbedroom main house and 
fourbedroom annex said norma dougherty rveha executive director 
it was a new idea shared living was not a real popular idea with 
seniors 
many wanted their own apartment and were reluctant to squeeze a 
lifetimes belongings into a bedroom dougherty said and for many 
tam house also is the first time theyve lived with a group since 
they were youngsters 
tam house is the product of a group of local church members who 
started meeting in 1975 to discuss senior housing in 1980 they 
found the house which was bought and renovated with federal 
development funds 
residents must be at least 55 and able to live independently 
when they move in rents range from 400 to 425 a month including 
dinner and food for doityourself breakfasts operating costs were 
78780 in 1988 dougherty said 
